00:01:37.614 --> 00:01:40.570
but for beginners, it's probably useful to think about it

00:01:40.569 --> 00:01:43.704
that way because you're sharing a Colonel with the underlying OS.

00:01:43.704 --> 00:01:46.500
So, since it's not a full Virtual machine,

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:50.769
what makes it Containers special or better that they're not?

00:01:50.769 --> 00:01:54.289
What are the advantages of not having them as a full Virtual Machine?

00:01:54.290 --> 00:01:56.530
Well, because they're not a full Virtual Machine,

00:01:56.530 --> 00:01:58.525
it's lighter weight on the OS,

00:01:58.525 --> 00:02:03.170
which means the applications can run with very low overhead.

00:02:03.170 --> 00:02:06.170
So, you don't pay a huge penalty for using the Container.

00:02:06.170 --> 00:02:11.879
